"author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "#### What is the problem?\r\n\r\nif during `rerun` command fails we would just end up in some branch or detached HEAD, possibly in a dirty repository.  \r\nIt would be nice to be able to retrospect \r\n- the logs from ran command\r\n- the commit message of the original commit we were rerunning (might have precious notes)\r\nand decide what to do, either\r\n- `save` and `--continue` or \r\n- `--abort` (so similar to merge and cherry-pick git commands).\r\n\r\nThe same would be applicable to when we start to handle merges\r\n", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/2092/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/2092/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}